d 'XTFACTORTEST': module to compute specification tests for heterogeneous panel data models with interactive (multifactor) error effects
d
d     xtfactortest is a Stata library implementing a coherent
d battery of specification tests    for heterogeneous panel data
d models.     Such Interactive-Effects (IE) panels nest both the
d standard two-way fixed effects (2W-FE)    model and the Common
d Correlated Effects (CCE) framework of Pesaran (2006).  Whether or
d    not a researcher needs CCE / PC depends on two concurrent
d issues:	 (a) whether the slopes beta_i are heterogeneous
d and, if so, whether that	      heterogeneity is correlated
d with VARIANCE features of the regressors (Campello,		
d Galvao & Juhl 2019);	      (b) whether the regressors are
d correlated with the unobserved factor loadings gamma_i	   
d (Bai 2009; Kapetanios, Serlenga & Shin 2023, 2024).	
d xtfactortest answers each question with a dedicated test plus a
d joint test, and provides    an explicit decision rule based on
d the five-lessons review of Juodis & Reese (2026). 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: specification tests
d KW: multifactor effects
d
d Requires: Stata version 16
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260513
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtfactortest.ado
f xtfactortest.sthlp
